referenceFunction.name: cream, at processing facility/US S
referenceFunction.generalComment: Inventory refers to the production of 1 kg of cream at processing facility in US. This system process includes raw milk inputs, electricity usage, fuel usage, chemical usage including refrigerants and cleaners, transportation operation, water usage, ammonia emission and sewage whey digestion wastewater treatment (national average wastewater treatment from 50 plant survey).

geography.text: Refers to an average production in the USA

technology.text: conventional technology typical for the country

timePeriod.text: The yield data have been collected for the years 2005-2009.

representativeness.samplingProcedure: Data were compiled from USDA NASS Agricultural statistics, literature processing plant survey, and expert knowledge.

source.text: This article presents a cradle-to-grave analysis of the United States fluid milk supply chain greenhousegas (GHG) emissions that are accounted from fertilizer production through consumption and disposal of milk packaging. Crop production and on-farm GHG emissions were evaluated using public data and 536 farm operation surveys. Milk processing data were collected from 50 dairy plants nationwide. Retail and consumer GHG emissions were estimated from primary data, design estimates, and publicly available data.
source.title: Greenhousegasemissions from milkproduction and consumption in the United States: A cradle-to-grave life cycle assessment circa 2008. Regional analysis of greenhouse gas emissions from USA dairy farms: A cradle to farm-gate assessment of the American dairy industry circa 2008.

validation.otherDetails: Peer reviewed: Olivier Jolliet (University of Michigan) Robert Anex (Iowa State University) Pascal Lesage (Sylvatica)
